text: Central Ostrobothnia is a region in western Finland. As of November 2013, almost 70,000 people lived there. Neighbouring regions are Ostrobothnia, Northern Ostrobothnia, Central Finland and Southern Ostrobothnia. == Municipalities == Central Ostrobothnia has 8 municipalities, two of those are cities (marked bold). * Halsua * Kannus * Kaustinen * Kokkola * Lestij√§rvi * Perho * Toholampi * Veteli == Other websites == * Official website Category:Central Ostrobothnia
